<H1>Administration Online Help</H1></A>
<P>Welcome to the administration help page.  This document contains information about the following topics: 
<P><A HREF="#intro">Introduction</A>: Provides a brief overview of the administration application.
<P><A HREF="#Procedures">Procedures</A>: Describes how to change your printer, region, modem, and monitor settings.
<P><A HREF="#Toolbar">Using the Toolbar</A>: Describes the administration toolbar functions.
<P><A HREF="ncfrescointernal:cancel">Return to Administration</A>: Closes this help page and returns you to the administration application.

<P><H2><A NAME="intro">Introduction</A></H2>
<P>The administration application allows you to configure your NC to the location where you use it (regional settings and modem) and the hardware you attach to it (printer and monitor). Additionally, you can obtain information about the version numbers of the applications contained in the NC.<P>

<A HREF="#top">[Top of Document]</A>
<A HREF="#Procedures">[Procedures]</A>
<A HREF="#Toolbar">[Using the Toolbar]</A>
<A HREF="ncfrescointernal:cancel">[Return to Administration]</A><BR><HR>

<A NAME="Procedures"><H2>Procedures</H2></A>
<P>This section covers the following topics:

<P><A HREF="#PROC1">Printer Configuration</A>
<P><A HREF="#PROC2">Regional Settings</A>
<P><A HREF="#PROC3">Modem Settings</A>
<P><A HREF="#PROC4">Monitor Settings</A>
<P><A HREF="#PROC5">Version Information</A>
<P><A HREF="#PROC6">Quitting the Administration Application</A>

<P><H3><A NAME="PROC1">Printer Configuration</A></H3>
The printer option allows you to configure your NC for the attached printer.
<OL><LI>Click on the <IMG WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=25 SRC="icontype:nc_vprnt"> button.
<LI>Click the display field and select your printer from the pop-up menu.
<LI>Choose the <i>Color printing</i> option if you require it.
<LI>Click on the <B>Save</B> button.</OL>
The NC is configured for your printer.

<P><H3><A NAME="PROC2">Regional Settings</A></H3>
The region option allows you to control localized aspects of your NC.
<OL><LI>Click on the <IMG WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=25 SRC="icontype:nc_vregi"> button.
<LI>Choose either <i>UK</i> or <i>USA</i>, depending on the location of the NC.
<LI>Click the time zone field and select the current time zone from the pop-up menu.
<LI>Choose the <i>Daylight saving time</i> option if you require it.
<LI>Click on the <B>Save</B> button.</OL>
The NC is configured for its current location.

<P><H3><A NAME="PROC3">Modem Settings</A></H3>
The modem setting allows you to configure your NC for the phone system it will use. <B>Note: </B>The modem settings option will only be available if you are using an modem based NC. 
<OL><LI>Click on the <IMG WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=25 SRC="icontype:nc_vmode"> button.
<LI>Choose either <i>Tone dialing</i> or <i>Pulse dialing</i>, depending on the phone exchange used.
<LI>Enter the local area phone code in the area code field.
<LI>If you need to obtain an outside line before dialing enter the number in the outside line field.
<LI>Choose the <i>Wait for second dial tone before dialing</i> option if the phone exchange requires it.
<LI>Click the modem disconnection field and select the time you require from the pop-up menu.
<LI>Click on the <B>Save</B> button.</OL>
The NC is configured for the phone system it will use.

<P><H3><A NAME="PROC4">Monitor Settings</A></H3>
The monitor settings allows you to configure your NC for the attached monitor. <B>Note: </B>The monitor settings option will not be available if you are using a television monitor with your NC. 
<OL><LI>Click on the <IMG WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=25 SRC="icontype:nc_vmoni"> button.
<LI>Click the monitor field and select the display you require from the pop-up menu.
<LI>Choose the <i>Use higher frame rate</i> option if you require it.
<LI>Click on the <B>Try</B> button.
<LI>If the display you have chosen is suitable for your monitor, click the <B>Save</B> button. Otherwise, click <B>Cancel</B> or wait 5 seconds.</OL>
The NC is configured for your monitor.

<P><H3><A NAME="PROC5">Version Information</A></H3>
The version option displays details of the version numbers of the applications present in ROM.
<OL><LI>Click on the <IMG WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=25 SRC="icontype:nc_vvers"> button.
<LI>Click on the <B>Continue</B> button.</OL>
The version window is closed.

<P><H3><A NAME="PROC6">Quitting the Administration Application</A></H3>
You can exit the administration application at any time by clicking on the <IMG WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=25 SRC="icontype:nc_vclos"> button.
<P>The administration application quits and you are returned to your starting point.<P>

